                    <h2 class="text-2xl font-black text-brandBlue uppercase italic mb-6">1. Why Does Shipping Matter for Charger Imports?</h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">Shipping costs can account for 5-30% of your total product cost when importing from China. Miscalculating these costs is one of the most common mistakes new importers make. This often leads to margin compression or pricing that's uncompetitive in the market.</p>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">At WOWOHCOOL, we've helped over 500 brands navigate the complexities of <a href="/service/" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">importing from China</a> since 2013. Our logistics team coordinates daily with freight forwarders across all major shipping routes, ensuring competitive rates and reliable delivery schedules for <a href="/products/wireless-charger/" class="text-brandBlue hover:text-brandOrange font-semibold">wireless chargers</a> and all our products.</p>
                    <div class="bg-brandBlue/5 rounded-xl p-6 mb-6">
                        <h3 class="font-black text-brandBlue uppercase mb-3">Shipping Cost Impact</h3>
                        <ul class="text-slate-600 text-sm space-y-2 list-disc pl-5">
                            <li>Shipping averages 8-15% of total landed cost for standard orders.</li>
                            <li>Air freight can add $0.50-2.00 per unit versus sea freight.</li>
                            <li>Express shipping (DHL, FedEx, UPS) adds $2-5 per unit for small orders.</li>
                            <li>Dimensional weight pricing can double shipping costs for light products.</li>
                            <li>The end of the $800 de minimis means every parcel now carries the full duty stack: MFN rate plus up to 25% Section 301 on HTS 8504 chargers.</li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
